Petathal was a large island located somewhere west across the sea from Faer√ªn, and south of the Korinn Archipelago.
Some time before the 13 century DR,This approximated date was derived from the [http//web.archive.org/web/20090602124758/http//www.wizards.com/default.asp?x=dnd/drfe/20080110&pf=true Grand History of the Realms The Moonshaes] stating that Viledel settled the land in 1228 DR and the adventure itself stating, "The Korinn Archipelago was discovered about 200 years ago . . . From 140 years ago to 100 years ago, the pirates reigned supreme..." this chain of islands was conquered by Northlanders. Later in 1228 DR, a noble adventurer from this island named Viledel led a band of humans and demihumans across the sea to the Korinn Archipelago, seeking to colonize the lands and aspiring to one day create a strong maritime empire.
